DATA CLOUD
Delete Records Using a Delete File

You can delete data records that are ingested using the AWS S3, Google Cloud Storage (GCS), Microsoft Azure, Ingestion API, or SFTP connector by creating a delete file in either CSV or Parquet file format. Parquet file ingestion is only supported by S3, GCS and, Azure data streams.

IMPORTANT When you delete more than 600,000 records between refreshes from your connected CRM instance, the data stream does a full refresh of your data.
Create a delete file with the list of primary keys of the corresponding records that you want to delete from your data stream.
The primaryKey field in the delete file must match the primary key data type of the data lake object (DLO). For example, if the DLO primary key field is a number, the delete file primaryKey data type must be a number.
If you’re deleting records ingested from a CSV file, create a headerless delete file in CSV format.
If you’re deleting records ingested from a Parquet file, create a Parquet delete file with a single column named primaryKey.
Name the delete file with the prefix Deletion_ and the name matching the source file.
For example, a file named Customer*, which contains a wildcard, is named Deletion_Customer.csv or Deletion_Customer.parquet.
In the directory where the source files are ingested from, create a subfolder named delete.
Upload the delete file to the delete folder.
EXAMPLE

The file with deletion records must be prefixed with "Deletion_" and must be placed under a separate folder "delete". For example if your stream is configured to ingest a file called accounts-file using a wildcard of accounts-* from a bucket accounts-bucket, and folder, accounts-folder. To delete records you must create a folder under the accounts-folder called delete.

If you're using CSV file then create a file called Deletion_accounts-.csv or if you're using Parquet Deletion_accounts-.parquet. You have a folder structure accounts-folder/delete/Deletion_accounts-.csv or accounts-folder/delete/Deletion_accounts-.parquet.

Sample CSV delete file


    0000-0000-0000
    0000-0000-0001
    0000-0000-0002
   

Sample Parquet delete file


    primaryKey
    0000-0000-0000
    0000-0000-0001
    0000-0000-0002
